f:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bybit calculates ETHFI/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using the premium/discount between perpetual and spot prices. The funding rate is capped at ±0.75% per interval to prevent extreme rates. Traders holding long positions pay funding when rates are positive, while short position holders receive payments. Bybit's unified margin allows seamless hedging across spot and derivatives without separate collateral requirements."}]
10:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","ETHFI","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ETHFI represents the EtherFi liquid restaking protocol, making it sensitive to Ethereum staking yield fluctuations and DeFi sentiment shifts. The token's smaller trading volume compared to major assets can lead to higher funding rate volatility, creating profitable arbitrage windows. DeFi tokens like ETHFI often experience funding rate spikes during sector rotations or protocol updates."}]]}]
11:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ETHFI funding rates on Bybit have shown significant volatility correlating with liquid staking developments and Ethereum ecosystem updates. During DeFi bull phases, ETHFI perpetuals often trade at substantial premiums with funding rates exceeding 0.1% per 8-hour period. The token exhibits higher funding rate variance than established assets due to its niche focus on liquid restaking. Weekend periods typically see reduced funding pressure as institutional activity decreases. Monitoring EigenLayer developments and restaking TVL changes helps predict funding rate movements for ETHFI."}]]}]
12:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ETHFI funding arbitrage works best during high volatility periods when perpetual premiums spike above 0.05% per funding interval. Bybit's unified margin enables efficient delta-neutral strategies by longing ETHFI spot while shorting perpetuals, capturing funding payments. The smaller market cap makes ETHFI susceptible to funding rate dislocations during news events or broader DeFi sector movements. Cross-exchange arbitrage with ETHFI spot on other platforms can enhance returns when Bybit perpetuals trade at significant premiums. Position sizing should account for ETHFI's lower liquidity compared to major cryptocurrencies."}]]}]
13:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ETHFI's exposure to Ethereum staking risks and smart contract vulnerabilities creates additional basis risk beyond typical funding arbitrage. The token's limited trading history means funding rate patterns may not be as predictable as established cryptocurrencies. Bybit's 0.055% taker fees can erode profits from frequent rebalancing, requiring careful position management. Slippage risk increases during volatile periods due to ETHFI's smaller order book depth. Regulatory changes affecting liquid staking protocols could impact ETHFI's fundamental value and funding rate dynamics."}]]}]
14:["$","$L16",null,{"items":[{"question":"What are typical ETHFI funding rates on Bybit?","answer":"ETHFI funding rates on Bybit typically range from -0.02% to +0.08% per 8-hour interval, with higher volatility during DeFi sector movements. Rates can spike above 0.1% during bullish periods or protocol announcements affecting EtherFi's liquid restaking platform."},{"question":"How does Bybit's unified margin help with ETHFI arbitrage?","answer":"Bybit's unified margin allows traders to use the same collateral for ETHFI spot and perpetual positions without separate margin requirements. This enables efficient delta-neutral funding arbitrage strategies and reduces capital requirements for hedged positions."},{"question":"What makes ETHFI funding rates more volatile than major cryptocurrencies?","answer":"ETHFI's smaller market cap and focus on liquid restaking create higher sensitivity to Ethereum staking developments and DeFi sector sentiment. The limited trading volume compared to BTC or ETH means funding rates can move more dramatically with relatively small capital flows."},{"question":"When are the best times to trade ETHFI funding arbitrage on Bybit?","answer":"ETHFI funding arbitrage opportunities typically peak during Ethereum network upgrades, EigenLayer announcements, or broader DeFi rallies when perpetual premiums spike. The 8-hour funding intervals at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC provide regular opportunities to capture rate differentials."}]}]
